'''Andries Van Aarde''' (born 1951) is an honorary professor of [[theology]] and a [[research fellow]] at the [[University of Pretoria]].<ref>[http://web.up.ac.za/default.asp?ipkCategoryID=15815&subid=15815 Prof Andries van Aarde]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, University of Pretoria</ref><ref>[http://www.westarinstitute.org/Fellows/aarde.html Andries van Aarde Chairperson, Department of New Testament Studies, University of Pretoria, South Africa] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111109232005/http://www.westarinstitute.org/Fellows/aarde.html |date=9 November 2011 }}
</ref><ref name=devilliers2011>[[De Villiers, G.]], 2011, ‘Andries van Aarde – [http://www.hts.org.za/index.php/HTS/article/view/1033/html#1 ''A sideways glance: His theological and hermeneutical contribution to the South African scene''], HTS Teologiese Studies/Theological Studies 67(1), Art. #1033, 10 pages. [http://www.hts.org.za/index.php/HTS/article/view/1033 doi.10.4102/hts.v67i1.1033]. {{ISSN|0259-9422}} (print) {{ISSN|2072-8050}} (online). This work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution License. [https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/ Attribution 3.0 Unported (CC BY 3.0)]</ref> He is also an ordained minister in the [[Netherdutch Reformed Church of Africa]].<ref name=devilliers2011/> He has shown interest in the ''[[Historical Jesus]]'' debate.<ref name=devilliers2011/>

