'''Arnold Otto Erich Brandenburg''' (31 July 1868 in [[Stralsund]] – 22 January 1946 in [[Leipzig]]) was a [[German people|German]] [[historian]].
His main work ''Die Reichsgründung'' ("The Founding of the Reich", 2 vols. plus 1 vol. with documents) covers the origins of the modern German national movement and the founding of the [[German Empire|Second Empire]] by [[Otto von Bismarck|Bismarck]]. The German historian [[Hans Herzfeld]] calls it "critical and reliable in its judgment" ("solide und kritisch zuverlässig im Urteil")<ref>Hans Herzfeld: Die moderne Welt 1789-1945. 1. Teil: Die Epoche der bürgerlichen Nationalstaaten. 6., revised edition. Braunschweig 1969, p. 157</ref> and Herbert Helbig in [[Neue Deutsche Biographie]] "objective, deliberate and not without a critical attitude towards the problems of Bismarck's Empire" ("sachlich, kühl und nicht ohne kritische Einstellung zu der inneren Problematik des Bismarckreiches").<ref>Herbert Helbig: Brandenburg, Erich. In: Neue Deutsche Biographie (NDB). Vol 2. Berlin 1955, p. 517.</ref>
In 1933 Brandenburg signed the ''[[w:de:Bekenntnis der deutschen Professoren zu Adolf Hitler|Loyalty Oath of German Professors to Adolf Hitler and the National Socialist State]]''.
== Literary works (selection) == * ''Die [[Revolutions of 1848 in the German states|deutsche Revolution 1848]]'', 1912 ([https://archive.org/details/diedeutscherevol00branuoft online]) * ''Die Reichsgründung'', 2 vols., 1916/1923 (online: [https://archive.org/details/diereichsbegrn01branuoft volume 1] [https://archive.org/details/diereichsbegrn02branuoft volume 2]) * ''Die materialistische Geschichtsauffasung'', 1920 * ''Von [[Otto von Bismarck|Bismarck]] zum Weltkriege'', 1924 ** ''From Bismarck to the World War: A History of German Foreign Policy 1870-1914'' (1933) [https://www.questia.com/library/1369211/from-bismarck-to-the-world-war-a-history-of-german online in English at Questia]
