'''Keyan Gray Tomaselli''' is a [[South Africa|South African]] communication professor and author, currently Professor Emeritus and Fellow at [[University of KwaZulu-Natal]], where he established and operated its Centre for Communication, Media and Society for 29 years until becoming a Distinguished Professor of Humanities at [[University of Johannesburg]]. He is also Editor of the UKZN-UJ journal ''Critical Arts:  South-North Cultural and Media Studies'' and co-editor at UJ's journal ''Journal of African Cinemas''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://ccms.ukzn.ac.za/staff/keyan-tomaselli.aspx |title=Keyan Tomaselli |publisher=ukzn.ac.za |accessdate=November 30, 2016}}</ref> He is also a published author and has been largely collected by libraries.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.worldcat.org/identities/lccn-n78009230/ |title=Tomaselli, Keyan G. |publisher=worldcat.org |accessdate=November 30, 2016}}</ref>

