[[File:CSU Rhodes Tower.jpg|thumb|Ronald E. Powaski has lectured at [[Cleveland State University]].]] '''Ronald E. Powaski''' is an American [[historian]] who has written on the [[Contemporary history|20th century]] [[foreign policies]] of the [[United States history|United States]] and [[European history|Europe]].
Powaski earned his Ph.D. in 1972 from [[Case Western Reserve University]] in [[Cleveland, Ohio]].<ref> * {{Cite thesis|title=Great Britain and the Manchurian crisis, 1931-1933 |first=Ronald Edward |last=Powaski |publisher=[[Case Western Reserve University]] |year=1972 |pages=880 }}</ref>
Powaski taught [[United States history|history]] at [[Euclid High School|Euclid Senior High School]] in [[Euclid, Ohio]].<ref>Powaski's high school teaching is noted in the following collection (which lists him as an advisor) on page 502: * {{cite book |pages=528 |editor=Peter B. Levy |title=100 Key Documents in American Democracy (Paperback) |publisher=Praeger |year=1999 |isbn= 978-0275965259 }} </ref> He has taught at several colleges and universities near Cleveland, particularly at [[Cleveland State University]].<ref> * {{cite book|title=Return to Armageddon: The United States and the Nuclear Arms Race, 1981-1999 |first=Ronald E. |last=Powaski |authorlink=Ronald E. Powaski |isbn=978-0-19-516098-7 |year=2003 |publisher=Oxford University Press }}</ref>
[[File:16May-21May Battle of Belgium.PNG|thumb|300px|Ronald E. Powaski has written a book on the [[blitzkrieg]] campaign of the [[German military]] in [[World War II]].]] Powaski's most recent book concerns the "[[blitzkrieg]]" attack by the German military in Western Europe.
